  "name": "Acts 3:11–26",
  "localizedName": "Acts 3:11–26",
  "content": [
    {
      "tiptap": {
        "type": "doc",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "When the beggar was healed, the crowd was amazed. For Peter, it was a chance to announce the good news about Jesus."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Peter made it clear that the God of Israel had healed the man who couldn’t walk. He did it through Peter and "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108542",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "John"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " because they "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108255",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "believed in"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " Jesus the Messiah."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The people listening to Peter were guilty of putting Jesus to death. But God raised Jesus from the dead."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108300",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Moses"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ", "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108452",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Samuel"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " and other prophets had spoken about these things before they happened."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Peter said that God makes everything new. He was talking about the "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108543",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "new creation"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ". Peter urged the people to turn away from evil and sin. Then they could receive the blessings of Jesus their Messiah."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
